				udptools

This is a simple pair of utilities to transmit and receive UDP packets.

The original purpose was for U-APSD manual unit testing, where it was
used to queue delivery frames from server to STA, then send trigger
frame(s) upstream.

It's possible to test WMM by sending packets with the UP (User Priority)
field in QoS Control set to desired values using the -t option.  For
example, -t224 or -t0xe0 is voice (UP=7); in general, shift the UP left
by 5.

To run under Windows XP, compile the utilities under Cygwin and make
sure DisableUserTOSSetting is set on the machine (search Twiki to see
how to do this).

udpsend
-------

Transmits one or more UDP packet(s) to a destination.

Usage: udpsend [options] <ip-addr>
   -p <port>     Specify UDP destination port (0-65535, default 6000)
   -t <tos>      IP TOS value; default 0x0
   -c <count>    Specify number of packets to send; 0 to loop until interrupted
   -s <size>     Specify size of UDP payload (1-3000, default 64)
   -w <usec>     Specify wait time after each packet
   -n <seq_no>   Specify starting sequence number, default 1

udprecv
-------

Listens for UDP packets and displays them.

Usage: udprecv [options]
   -p <port>     Specify UDP listen port (0-65535, default 6000)
   -q            Do not display packets received
   -c <count>    Exit after receiving <count> packets
   -w <usec>     Exit if no packets are received for <usec> microseconds
